==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rife
<hw>Rife</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>r⟦imac⟧f</ets>
abundant, or Icel. <ets>r⟦imac⟧fr</ets> munificent; akin to OD.
<ets>riff</ets>, <ets>rijve</ets>, abundant.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Prevailing; prevalent; abounding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Before the plague of London, inflammations of the lungs were
<qex>rife</qex> and mortal.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Even now the tumult of loud mirth⟦br⟧
Was <qex>rife</qex>, and perfect in may listening ear.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having power; active; nimble.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What! I am <qex>rife</qex> a little yet.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Rife"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Rife"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riffle</ent>⟦br⟧
